<TITLE> British police face probe over man`s car death </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 London, Feb 9 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Britain's Independent Police Complaints Commission (IPCC) has launched an investigation into the death of a man following a police chase in the south coast city of Brighton on Saturday. A car carrying five people crashed following the chase after police had signalled to it to stop, said the IPCC, which has sent two investigators to the scene. Another of the car's passengers is critically ill in the Royal Sussex County hospital. "My condolences go to the family and friends of the dead man," said IPCC Commissioner Tom Davies. "This must have been a traumatic incident for everybody involved, including the members of the emergency services who attended. "The IPCC investigation will be independent and proportionate.
